metadata.name: Tepezza 500 mg 1 Injection powder lyophilized for solution

clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Teprotumumab is indicated for the treatment of thyroid eye disease L11359

contraindications.disease: Toxicity information including information regarding overdosage is currently unavailable L11359 Symptoms of teprotumumab overdose are likely to be consistent with its adverse effect profile
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Teprotumumab inhibits the downstream effects of IGF 1R signaling namely tissue inflammation and remodeling which are responsible for the various symptoms of thyroid eye disease L11359 A190138 Teprotumumab may cause disease flares in patients with pre existing inflammatory bowel disease IBD patients experiencing an exacerbation should discontinue therapy with teprotumumab Significant hyperglycemia has been observed in patients receiving treatment with teprotumumab which may require antihyperglycemic medications Based on its mechanism of action it is likely that teprotumumab will cause fetal harm in pregnant woman for this reason females of child bearing age should use effective contraception prior to initiation during therapy and for 6 months following the last dose of teprotumumab L11359
